{
  "attrs": {
    "abstract": "This dataset provides a Climate Data Record of Sea Ice Thickness for the Northern Hemisphere polar region, derived from the SIRAL (SAR Interferometer Radar ALtimeter) instrument on the CryoSat-2 satellite at Level 3C (L3C). This product was generated in the context of the ESA Climate Change Initiative Programme (ESA CCI) by the Sea Ice CCI (Sea_Ice_cci) project.\n\nIt provides monthly gridded sea ice thickness data on a Lambeth Azimuthal Equal Area grid for the period November 2010 to April 2020. Data are only available for the NH winter months, October - April.",
    "catalog_url": "https://catalogue.ceda.ac.uk/uuid/45b5b1e556da448089e2b57452f277f5",
    "cci_project": "SEAICE",
    "comment": "Northern hemisphere sea ice thickness coverage is limited to the winter month between October and April due to negative effect of surface melt on the retrieval of freeboard. Please consult the Product User Guide (PUG) for more information.",
    "data_type": "SITHICK",
    "ecv": "SEAICE",
    "history": "20240220T150152Z - Product generated with pysiral version 0.9.6",
    "institute": "Alfred-Wegener-Institut Helmholtz-Zentrum f\u00fcr Polar- und Meeresforschung",
    "platform_id": "CryoSat-2",
    "processing_level": "L3C",
    "product_string": "NH25KMEASE2",
    "product_version": "3-0",
    "project": "Climate Change Initiative - European Space Agency",
    "publication_date": "2024-04-02T14:54:27",
    "references": "CCI+ Sea Ice ECV - Sea Ice Thickness Algorithm Theoretical Basis Document (ATBD)https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10605840; CCI+ Sea Ice ECV - Sea Ice Thickness Product User Guide (PUG) https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10605998",
    "sensor_id": "SIRAL",
    "source": "Altimetry: cryosat2, Snow depth: Monthly climatology based on regional merging of Warren Climatology with 50% reduction for first-year sea ice in the central Arctic and AMSR-2 based snow depth from IUP Bremen in remaining ice-covered regions, Mean Sea Surface: DTU21 global mean sea surface, Sea ice Concentration: C3S Sea Ice Concentration CDR/ICDR v3.0, Sea ice type: C3S Sea Ice Type CDR/ICDR v3.0, Region code: NSIDC regional mask for Arctic sea ice trends and climatologies (J. Scott Stewart and Walter N. Meier (2021), NSIDC)",
    "title": "ESA Sea Ice Climate Change Initiative (Sea_Ice_cci): Northern hemisphere sea ice thickness from the CryoSat-2 satellite on a monthly grid (L3C), v3.0",
    "uuid": "45b5b1e556da448089e2b57452f277f5"
